.md) unless you explicitly test for the variable as an HRESULT. This warning is off by default.  \n  \n## Example  \nThe following sample generates C4165  \n  \n```cpp  \n// C4165.cpp  \n// compile with: /W1  \n#include <windows.h>  \n#pragma warning(1:4165)  \n  \nextern HRESULT hr;  \nint main() {  \n   if (hr) {  \n   // try either of the following ...  \n   // if (FAILED(hr)) { // C4165 expected  \n   // if (hr != S_OK) {  \n   }  \n}  \n```"}